font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
```

Both fonts are loaded via Google Fonts CDN (not self-hosted).

### Font Weights

| Weight | Name | Usage |
|--------|------|-------|
| **400** | Regular | Body text, descriptions |
| **500** | Medium | Captions, emphasis, h3/h4 headings |
| **600** | SemiBold | Available for strong emphasis |
| **700** | Bold | Display headings, hero text |
| **900** | Black | Maximum impact, logos, hero display |

### Type Scale (base = 16px)

BFD uses a compact type scale. Hierarchy is achieved through weight and tracking, not just size.

| Element | Size | Line Height | Weight | Tracking |
|---------|------|-------------|--------|----------|
| **Display** | 3rem → 4.5rem (responsive) | 1.1 | 700 | -0.02em |
| **h1** | 1.5rem (24px) | 1.1 | 400 | -0.02em |
| **h2** | 1.25rem (20px) | 1.25 | 400 | -0.01em |
| **h3** | 1.125rem (18px) | 1.3 | 500 | -0.01em |
| **h4** | 1rem (16px) | 1.35 | 500 | 0 |
| **Body** | 0.875rem (14px) | 1.6 | 400 | 0 |
| **Caption** | 0.75rem (12px) | 1 | 500 | 0.1em / UPPERCASE |

### Typography Rules

1. **Hierarchy through weight and tracking** — h2 and h3 differ more by weight (400 vs 500) than by size
2. **Only Captions are uppercase** — Everything else is sentence case
3. **Brand name is Title Case:** "Black Flag Design" (never "black flag design" or "BLACK FLAG DESIGN")
4. **Tight negative tracking** on headings (-0.02em to -0.01em) for a confident feel
5. **Colors:** Light backgrounds → `#171717` (bf-text). Dark backgrounds → `#F2F2F2` (bf-dark-text)

### CSS Classes

